    text: 'A model-driven app has the following JavaScript code attached to the OnChange event of the Phone (telephone1) field on the Account entity:\n\n- If telephone1 is null, the code returns.\n- Otherwise, it reads primarycontactid and calls Xrm.WebApi.updateRecord("contact", contact[0].id, { telephone1: telephone }).\n- On success it shows an alert dialog with "Updated".\n- On failure it shows an alert dialog with "Not updated".\n\nFor each statement, determine whether it is true.\n\nSTATEMENTS:\n1. When the code runs and the Primary contact (primarycontactid) field is populated, the Contact record\'s Phone (telephone1) field is updated to match the Account.\n2. When the code runs and the Primary contact (primarycontactid) field is not populated, the following error message displays: Not updated.\n3. When the code runs and the value in Phone (telephone1) is removed, the Contact record\'s Phone (telephone1) field is updated to null.',
